# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if having platform-specific dependencies or dependencies
#   having no cross-platform support, pipenv may install dependencies that don't work, or not
#   install all needed dependencies.
#Pipfile.lock

# uv
#   uv is used locally (see [tool.uv] in pyproject.toml), but the lockfile is not
#   committed: CI and the release workflow build with pip/hatchling, not `uv sync`,
#   so uv.lock is a local-dev artifact regenerated on demand. (Commit it instead if
#   CI is ever switched to `uv sync` for reproducible installs.)
uv.lock

